President Obama spoke with Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif of Pakistan to discuss bilateral and regional issues. They agreed to work together to strengthen U.S.-Pakistan relations and promote stability, security, and prosperity in Pakistan and the region. The President mentioned his recent visit to India and expressed support for efforts to improve ties between India and Pakistan. He also appreciated Pakistan's efforts in combating terrorism and welcomed the improved relations between Afghanistan and Pakistan. Both leaders expressed their intention to meet at a convenient time.